Real Madrid have announced that midfielder, James Rodriquez, has left the club to join Premier League side, Everton. The La Liga champions made this known in a statement on Monday night. The statement read: “Real Madrid CF and Everton FC have agreed to transfer the player James Rodríguez. “Real Madrid wants to show you its gratitude and affection for all this time you have been part of our club and wishes you good luck in this new stage of your professional career.” Rodriguez, 29, will now reunite with Carlo Ancelotti, who he worked under both at Real Madrid and at Bayern Munich.